06550nam a22009975i 9783110210781DE-B159720211217065530.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211217t20092009gw     fo  d z      ger d  a(OCoLC)774093310  a97831102107817 a10.1515/97831102107812doi  a(DE-B1597)35417  a(OCoLC)642685783  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 ager  agwcDE 4aPT2625.A44bZ5527 2009 7aLIT0041702bisacsh0481ua833.912qDE-101222/ger  aGM 47802rvk0(DE-625)rvk/42180:04aDie Erfindung des Schriftstellers Thomas Mann /chrsg. von Michael Ansel, Hans Edwin Friedrich, Gerhard Lauer. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2009] 4c©2009  a1 online resource (494 p.) :bZahlr. Abb.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThomas Mann is regarded as the best-known representative of modern German literature. This exceptional status is the result of very conscious work on his own profile. How did Thomas Mann manage to achieve this status as the representative of German literature? Which categories did he use to reflect on his role as a writer? And which alliances or conflicts determined the perception he had of himself and others had of him? What was the part played by his publishers, by German scholars and journalists in the augmentation of his fame? The answers to these questions show how Thomas Mann and both his patrons and his rivals worked to invent him as a writer. They open a new perspective on Thomas Mann and his work.  aThomas Mann ist durch sehr bewusste Strategien und Inszenierungen zu dem Thomas Mann geworden, als der er in die Literaturgeschichte eingegangen ist. Diesem Selbstentwurf des Autors Thomas Mann zum repräsentativen deutschen Schriftsteller geht der Sammelband nach. Er fragt nach der Semantik der Repräsentanz, die Thomas Mann gebraucht, analysiert die Stellung im literarischen Feld seiner Zeit und beschreibt die Apparate, die seinen Ruhm zu multiplizieren wussten. In der Summe entsteht ein Bild von Thomas Mann, das die gängigen werkbiographischen Zugänge überbieten möchte und danach fragt, weshalb solche Zugänge bis heute für die Rekonstruktion der Selbstvermarktungsstrategien dieses Autors maßgeblich geblieben sind.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aAutor. 4aMann, Thomas. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aAuthor.  aMann, Thomas.1 aAnsel, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnsel, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAuerochs, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBecker, Sabina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorchmeyer, Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDetering, Heinrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngel, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedrich, Hans Edwin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFriedrich, Hans-Edwin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaefs, Wilhelm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHagestedt, Lutz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanuschek, Sven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJahraus, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlausnitzer, Ralf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKontje, Todd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKurzke, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLauer, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.